        {
          "type": "explanation",
          "name": "Shield Impact Settings",
          "definition": "Plasma is computed as a threshold between the two noise textures.This threshold is then raised to the power of \"sharpness\", the \"threshold\" is subtracted,and the result is multiplied by \"scale\".There are 2 such bands of plasma, presumably 1 thick and 1 thin (based on the settings).Each band (1 & 2) has a color for shield impact and another color for overshield+invincibility.\n"
        },
